# Design agent — agent-browser

Use the global **`agent-browser`** CLI (not `npx`). Chrome is installed via `agent-browser install`.

## When to use

- **Reference sites:** User asks for UX inspiration, layout patterns, or “how does X site do Y?”
- **Local app:** After `cd web && npm run dev`, verify UI changes on `http://localhost:5173`
- **Dogfood / QA:** For systematic exploration, run `agent-browser skills get dogfood --full` and follow that workflow

## Do not use for

- **https://www.82-0.com/** — do not treat the original game as a design reference unless the user explicitly asks
- Replacing the data pipeline or BBRef scripts

## Standard workflow

```bash
agent-browser open <url>
agent-browser snapshot -i -c    # interactive elements with @refs
agent-browser screenshot        # optional visual evidence
agent-browser close
```

Use `@e1`, `@e2` refs from the snapshot for `click`, `fill`, `scroll`, etc.

## Local dev

1. Start dev server: `cd web && npm run dev`
2. Browse: `agent-browser open http://localhost:5173`
3. After UI edits, re-snapshot and screenshot before claiming done

## Output for the user

Summarize what you observed (layout, motion, typography, interaction patterns) and tie recommendations to files under `web/src/`. Save screenshots under the repo only if the user wants artifacts committed.
